    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1959-05-20T12:16:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1959-05-20T12:16:00-05:00" n="64"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d64">
                <head>64. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Embassy in Japan</gloss>
                    <note n="0" type="source" xml:id="d64fn0">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 611.94/5–2059. Confidential; <gloss target="#t_niact1">Niact</gloss>;
                        Limit Distribution. Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_SRL2"
                            >Sneider</persName> on May 18; cleared with L/FE, H in substance, and
                        with <gloss target="#t_DOD1">DOD</gloss>; and approved by <persName
                            corresp="#p_DCD1">Dillon</persName>. Repeated to <gloss
                            target="#t_CINCPAC1">CINCPAC</gloss> exclusive for <gloss
                            target="#t_POLAD1">POLAD</gloss> and Admiral <persName
                            corresp="#p_FAHD1">Felt</persName>, and to <gloss
                            target="#t_COMUSJAPAN1">COMUS/Japan</gloss> exclusive for General
                            <persName corresp="#p_BLGRW1">Burns</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1959-05-20T13:16:00-04:00">May 20, 1959, 1:16 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1757. For <persName corresp="#p_MADII1">MacArthur</persName> from <persName
                        corresp="#p_RWS1">Robertson</persName>. <gloss target="#t_Deptel1"
                        >Deptel</gloss> 1726.<note n="1" xml:id="d64fn1">
                        <ref target="#d60">Document 60</ref>.</note> Re Article XXV 2(b). We
                    agreeable to deleting Article XXV 2(b) providing for yen contribution in new
                    administrative arrangements. (<gloss target="#t_FYI1">FYI</gloss>. As soon as we
                    have reached agreement with <gloss target="#t_GOJ1">GOJ</gloss> on all major
                    substantive points, we intend <pb facs="0207" n="177" xml:id="pg_177"/> discuss
                    entire package with appropriate Congressional committees. End <gloss
                        target="#t_FYI1">FYI</gloss>)</p>
                <p>In interest of answering possible Congressional objections to dropping yen
                    contribution most helpful if <persName corresp="#p_FA8">Fujiyama</persName>
                    would affirm that <gloss target="#t_GOJ1">GOJ</gloss> intends take every
                    practicable measure assure that funds derived from absence yen contribution will
                    be used for Japanese defense forces.</p>
                <p>Defense concurs.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="strong">
                            <persName corresp="#p_DCD1">Dillon</persName>
                        </hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
